Political analyst Brutus Malada spoke with eNCA's Shahan Ramkissoon. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The ANC will oppose Ace Magashule's court attempt to overturn his suspension as SG.
On Monday, the suspended ANC Secretary-General was adamant he will never be banned from the party. READ: Magashule: I won't be banned from the ANC He was showing his support for former president Jacob Zuma outside the High Court in Pietermaritzburg. Magashule submitted a document to the High Court in Johannesburg regarding the step-aside resolution. READ: Defiant Magashule says he won't apologise He wants it declared unlawful, invalid and unconstitutional. The ANC met on Monday and decided they would oppose his application.